        "coral-reef": {
            "id": "coral-reef",
            "summary": "They learn that coral is actually alive‚Äîtiny animals called polyps",
            "text": "The mini-submarine descends through crystal-clear water. Suddenly, color explodes everywhere‚Äîthe coral reef!\n\n'People think coral is rock or plant,' Dr. Marina explains, 'but it's actually made of tiny animals called polyps. Each polyp is smaller than your fingernail, but together they build these massive structures over thousands of years.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} presses against the window in amazement. The coral comes in every color imaginable‚Äîpurple fans, orange branches, pink domes, yellow tubes.\n\n'Coral polyps have a special relationship with tiny algae that live inside them,' Dr. Marina continues. 'The algae use sunlight to make food through photosynthesis‚Äîjust like plants‚Äîand share that food with the coral. In return, the coral gives the algae a safe home. We call this symbiosis‚Äîtwo different species helping each other survive.'\n\nA clownfish darts into a swaying anemone. 'There's another symbiosis! The clownfish is immune to the anemone's sting. It gets protection, and the anemone gets cleaned and defended.'",
