        "twilight-zone": {
            "id": "twilight-zone",
            "summary": "The submarine descends to where sunlight barely reaches",
            "text": "The submarine's lights cut through increasingly dark water. The depth gauge reads 300 meters.\n\n'Welcome to the twilight zone,' Dr. Marina says softly. 'Below 200 meters, almost no sunlight reaches. The creatures here have adapted in amazing ways.'\n\nSuddenly, lights flash outside‚Äîbut not from the submarine. A jellyfish drifts past, glowing brilliant blue!\n\n'Bioluminescence!' Dr. Marina exclaims. 'Many deep-sea creatures make their own light through chemical reactions in their bodies. Some use it to attract prey, others to confuse predators, and some to communicate with each other.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} spots something large moving in the darkness. It has enormous eyes that seem to glow.\n\n'That's a giant squid eye,' Dr. Marina whispers. 'The largest eyes in the animal kingdom‚Äîas big as dinner plates! In the darkness, every bit of light matters. Big eyes help them spot predators and prey in the faintest glow.'",
