        "coral-bleaching": {
            "id": "coral-bleaching",
            "summary": "They see bleached coral and learn about warming oceans",
            "text": "Dr. Marina guides the submarine to a section of reef that looks different‚Äîthe coral is white, like bones.\n\n'This is coral bleaching,' she says sadly. 'When the ocean gets too warm, the coral gets stressed and expels the colorful algae living inside it. Without the algae, the coral turns white and slowly starves.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} looks devastated. 'Can it recover?'\n\n'Sometimes, if the water cools down quickly enough. But climate change is making the oceans warmer overall. The ocean absorbs over 90% of the extra heat trapped by greenhouse gases. Coral reefs are like the canaries in the coal mine‚Äîthey warn us that something is wrong.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} notices tiny fish swimming around the bleached coral, looking confused. 'What happens to all the animals that live here?'\n\n'Without healthy coral, they lose their homes and food sources. Coral reefs are called the rainforests of the sea‚Äîthey cover less than 1% of the ocean floor but support 25% of all marine species.'",
            "emoji": "üå°Ô∏è",
