        "cleaning-station": {
            "id": "cleaning-station",
            "summary": "They witness fish getting cleaned by tiny shrimp and wrasses",
            "text": "Dr. Marina points to a busy spot on the reef where several large fish are lined up, almost like they're waiting in line.\n\n'This is a cleaning station! Watch closely.'\n\nTiny bright blue fish swim right up to a big grouper's mouth‚Äîand go inside! {{PLAYER2_NAME}} gasps, but the grouper holds perfectly still.\n\n'Those are cleaner wrasses,' Dr. Marina explains. 'They eat parasites, dead skin, and bits of food stuck in the bigger fish's scales, gills, and teeth. It's a win-win: the cleaners get a meal, and the big fish get a spa treatment.'\n\nThe grouper opens its mouth wide, and the little cleaners swim in and out, picking off tiny organisms.\n\n'The amazing part is trust. The big fish could easily eat the cleaners, but they don't‚Äîbecause the service is too valuable. Fish travel long distances to visit reliable cleaning stations. Some scientists think these cleaners help reduce stress in their clients!'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} laughs. 'Fish dentists!'",
