        "giant-squid": {
            "id": "giant-squid",
            "summary": "They catch a glimpse of the legendary giant squid",
            "text": "The submarine's lights barely penetrate the darkness at 600 meters. Then, emerging from the black‚Äîtentacles!\n\nA giant squid, longer than a school bus, drifts past the window. Its huge eyes reflect the submarine's lights like two silver moons.\n\n'Incredible!' Dr. Marina breathes. 'Giant squid were considered mythical sea monsters for centuries. Sailors called them Kraken. We didn't get clear photos of a living one until 2004!'\n\nThe squid's skin flashes with patterns‚Äîbands of color rippling across its body.\n\n'Squid communicate through color changes! They have special cells called chromatophores that can change color in milliseconds. They use them for camouflage, hunting, and talking to each other.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} watches, mesmerized, as the giant slowly disappears back into the darkness. 'How do they survive the pressure down here?'\n\n'Their bodies don't have air spaces that can be crushed. Their cells are adapted to function under enormous pressure. Life finds a way to thrive even in the most extreme conditions.'",
