        "bioluminescence": {
            "id": "bioluminescence",
            "summary": "They learn about the chemistry of living light",
            "text": "Dr. Marina turns off the submarine's lights. For a moment, there's only darkness. Then, slowly, the ocean comes alive with light.\n\nBlue sparkles. Green flashes. Red pulses. It's like floating through a galaxy of stars.\n\n'About 90% of deep-sea creatures produce light,' Dr. Marina whispers. 'It's the most common form of communication in the ocean. The chemistry is beautiful‚Äîa molecule called luciferin reacts with oxygen, and the energy is released as light instead of heat.'\n\nAn anglerfish drifts past, its glowing lure dangling in front of its terrifying teeth.\n\n'The anglerfish uses its light to attract prey. Other fish see the glow, think it's something to eat, swim closer‚Äîand become dinner instead.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} points at a squid shooting out a cloud of glowing ink. 'What's that doing?'\n\n'That's a defense! Instead of black ink like shallow squid, deep-sea squid release glowing ink to blind and confuse predators while they escape. Isn't evolution amazing?'",
