        "otter-tools": {
            "id": "otter-tools",
            "summary": "They watch otters use rocks as tools to crack open shells",
            "text": "The sea otter floats on its back, and {{PLAYER1_NAME}} notices it has a rock balanced on its chest. The otter picks up a clam and smashes it against the rock‚Äîcrack! Dinner is served.\n\n'Sea otters are one of the few animals that use tools!' Dr. Marina says. 'They keep a favorite rock tucked in a pouch of skin under their armpit. Some otters use the same rock their whole lives.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} watches another otter wrap itself in kelp before falling asleep. 'Why is it doing that?'\n\n'So it doesn't drift away while napping! Kelp anchors them in place. Otters also hold hands while sleeping in groups‚Äîcalled rafts‚Äîso they stay together. A raft can have over 100 otters!'\n\nThe otter finishes its clam and rolls playfully in the water. Its fur glistens.\n\n'Otter fur is the densest of any mammal‚Äîup to one million hairs per square inch! They don't have blubber like whales, so that thick fur is the only thing keeping them warm. That's why oil spills are so devastating to them‚Äîif oil mats their fur, they can freeze to death.'",
