        "food-web": {
            "id": "food-web",
            "summary": "Dr. Marina explains how energy flows through the ecosystem",
            "text": "Dr. Marina pulls up a holographic display showing the kelp forest food web.\n\n'Everything is connected,' she explains. 'Energy starts with the kelp, which uses sunlight to grow. Small invertebrates eat the kelp. Small fish eat those invertebrates. Bigger fish eat the small fish. Sea lions eat those fish. And orcas eat the sea lions.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} traces the lines connecting species. 'What happens if one part disappears?'\n\n'The whole system can collapse. Remember the sea otters? When they were hunted nearly to extinction for their fur, sea urchins exploded in number and ate all the kelp. The fish that lived in the kelp disappeared. The animals that ate those fish left. Entire coastlines turned into barren rock.'\n\n'But when otters came back...'\n\n'Everything recovered! This is why we study these connections. Protecting one species often means protecting many others. Nature isn't a collection of separate things‚Äîit's a web, and every thread matters.'",
