            "summary": "They see scientists growing coral to restore damaged reefs",
            "text": "Dr. Marina takes them to a special area where structures underwater hold hundreds of small coral fragments.\n\n'This is a coral nursery! Scientists grow coral in protected conditions, then transplant them to damaged reefs. It's like gardening, but underwater.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} sees tiny corals growing on ceramic tiles and plastic structures. 'How long does it take?'\n\n'Years, unfortunately. Coral grows slowly. But we're learning to speed things up. Some corals are more heat-resistant than others‚Äîwe're breeding those tough ones to create reefs that can survive warming waters.'\n\nShe shows them another approach: 3D-printed reef structures. 'We design shapes that corals love to attach to, then sink them to create new foundations for reefs.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} watches a scientist carefully attach a coral fragment. 'Is it working?'\n\n'In some places, yes! Restored reefs are coming back to life‚Äîfish are returning, the ecosystem is healing. It gives us hope. But the biggest solution is still stopping climate change so we don't have to keep rescuing reefs.'",
