            "summary": "They learn about plastic pollution and how turtles mistake bags for jellyfish",
            "text": "The sea turtle suddenly changes direction, heading toward something floating in the water. Dr. Marina's expression darkens.\n\n'Quick, we need to intercept.' She maneuvers the submarine closer.\n\nThe turtle is approaching a plastic bag, drifting like a ghost in the current.\n\n'To a turtle, that looks exactly like a jellyfish‚Äîone of their favorite foods.' Dr. Marina uses the submarine's mechanical arm to grab the bag before the turtle can eat it. 'Plastic kills over 100,000 marine animals every year. They eat it, thinking it's food, and it blocks their digestive systems.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} looks horrified. 'Where does it all come from?'\n\n'Us. Humans produce 400 million tons of plastic every year, and millions of tons end up in the ocean. Some breaks into tiny pieces called microplastics that are now found everywhere‚Äîin the deepest trenches, in Arctic ice, even in fish we eat.'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} watches the turtle swim away safely. 'What can we do?'",
