            "text": "A massive shape moves through the darkness. It's a sperm whale‚Äîthe largest toothed predator on Earth!\n\n'Sperm whales dive deeper than any other mammal‚Äîover 2,000 meters!' Dr. Marina whispers. 'They hunt giant squid in the darkness. When scientists examine sperm whales, they often find circular scars from squid suckers‚Äîevidence of epic battles in the deep.'\n\nThe whale clicks‚Äîrapid, rhythmic sounds that seem to vibrate through the submarine.\n\n'Echolocation! Whales send out clicks and listen for echoes to build a picture of their surroundings. It's like seeing with sound. Sperm whale clicks are the loudest sounds made by any animal‚Äîover 230 decibels. That's louder than a jet engine!'\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} watches in awe as the whale glides past, its massive tail disappearing into the gloom.\n\n'Sperm whales can hold their breath for over an hour. Their blood and muscles hold much more oxygen than ours. Every part of their body is adapted for the deep‚Äîa masterpiece of evolution.'",
