            "summary": "Dr. Marina explains how scientists explore the deep ocean",
            "text": "'How do you study creatures that live in total darkness under crushing pressure?' Dr. Marina asks. 'Very carefully!'\n\nShe shows them images of different research tools. 'Remotely operated vehicles‚ÄîROVs‚Äîlet us explore without risking human lives. We can send them to depths no human could survive.'\n\nShe points to special collecting jars. 'When we bring deep-sea creatures to the surface, the pressure change can be deadly for them. We use special containers that maintain pressure during the trip up.'\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} looks at the glowing creatures outside. 'What have you discovered?'\n\n'New species all the time! We estimate there are millions of ocean species we haven't found yet. Just last year, we discovered fish living 8,300 meters deep‚Äîthe deepest ever recorded. And some organisms near hydrothermal vents have enzymes that work in extreme heat, which has helped us develop new medical treatments and industrial processes.'\n\n'The deep ocean is like another planet,' {{PLAYER1_NAME}} says.\n\n'Exactly! Except this alien world is right here on Earth.'",
